Start.

2. Input two matrices A and B in triplet form (row, column, value).

3. Initialize i, j, k = 1.

4. While i <= t1 and j <= t2:

• If positions match, add values.

• Else copy smaller element to result matrix.

5. Copy remaining elements from A or B.

6. Set header row with total non-zero count.

7. Print the resultant sparse matrix.

8. Stop.
